==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: earflap
<hw>earflap</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>one of two flaps attached to a cap
to keep the ears warm. On some hats the <ex>earflaps</ex> may be
adjusted or tied to the top of the hat, and lowered when needed in
colder weather.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> earlap.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

